body {
  font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
  font-size: 16px;
  font-size-adjust: 0.52; /* Example x-height ratio for 'Inter' */
}

h1 {
  font-family: 'Merriweather', serif, sans-serif;
  font-size: 2.5em;
  font-size-adjust: 0.45; /* Example x-height ratio for 'Merriweather' */
}

/* How to determine 'font-size-adjust' value:
   1. Measure the x-height and the overall font-size (em-square) of your desired font.
   2. Divide x-height by em-square (or cap-height for some contexts).
   3. Tools like Font Squirrel's @font-face generator often provide these metrics. */
